<sn><md>### Course Learning Outcomes (CLOs)

Upon completion, students will be able to:

* **CLO 1:** Acquire basic knowledge of general biochemistry and soil biochemistry.
* **CLO 2:** Understand soil health, plant growth, soil enzymes, and biogeochemical cycles.
* **CLO 3:** Understand macromolecule structure and their chemical and microbial decomposition in soil.
* **CLO 4:** Understand nitrogen fixation, nitrification, denitrification, rhizosphere, and mycorrhizal fungi.
</md></sn><sn><md>### Course Contents

| Topic                                 | Details                                                                                       |
| ------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Introduction**                      | Basic biochemistry<br>role in soil and environment<br>concepts of metabolism                  |
| **Enzymes**                           | Characteristics<br>functions<br>nomenclature<br>classification<br>mechanisms of enzyme action |
| **Carbohydrates**                     | Monosaccharides<br>polysaccharides<br>cellulose<br>starch<br>glucosamine<br>hemicellulose     |
| **Lignin and Chitin**                 | Occurrence<br>composition<br>importance<br>microbial decomposition factors                    |
| **Proteins**                          | Occurrence<br>composition<br>importance<br>microbial decomposition factors                    |
| **Biological Nitrogen Fixation**      | Symbiotic and non-symbiotic fixation<br>nodulation<br>cross-inoculation groups                |
| **Nitrification and Denitrification** | Mechanisms<br>factors<br>environmental consequences                                           |
| **Rhizosphere**                       | Concepts<br>types<br>agricultural significance                                                |
